---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';

const title = 'Percentage to CGPA Calculator';
const description =
  'Free percentage to CGPA calculator. Convert your percentage to CGPA using the common CBSE formula (percentage ÷ 9.5) or your own custom divisor.';
const intro =
  'Enter your percentage to convert it to CGPA. Uses the common CBSE formula (percentage ÷ 9.5) or your own divisor.';
const category = { id: 'everyday', name: 'Everyday' };
const faqs = [
  { q: 'How do I convert percentage to CGPA?', a: 'The common method divides your percentage by 9.5. For example, 76% ÷ 9.5 = 8.0 CGPA. The calculator handles this instantly.' },
  { q: 'Can I use a different divisor?', a: 'Yes — choose "Custom divisor" and enter the value your university uses instead of 9.5.' },
  { q: 'Is the result official?', a: 'It\'s an accurate estimate using a widely-used formula, but always confirm your institution\'s official method for formal applications.' },
  { q: 'What is the highest CGPA I can get?', a: 'That depends on your institution\'s scale. On a 10-point scale with the CBSE formula (÷9.5), 100% converts to approximately 10.53 CGPA, but most systems cap CGPA at 10.' },
  { q: 'What if my percentage is above 100?', a: 'The calculator will still compute a result, but double-check — percentages above 100 usually indicate extra credit or a scoring adjustment.' },
  { q: 'Can I convert CGPA to percentage?', a: 'Yes — use our <a href="/tools/cgpa-to-percentage" class="font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline">CGPA to Percentage Calculator</a> for the reverse conversion.' },
  { q: 'Which divisor should I use?', a: 'CBSE uses 9.5. Some universities use 9.0, 10, or other values. Check your institution\'s official conversion policy to be sure.' },
  { q: 'Is percentage to CGPA conversion common outside India?', a: 'The CGPA system is most common in India and parts of Asia. Other countries typically use GPA or direct percentage systems.' },
];
---

<ToolLayout title={title} description={description} intro={intro} category={category} faqs={faqs}>
  <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm sm:p-6">
    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <label class="block"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-700">Your percentage</span>
        <input id="pct" type="number" step="any" placeholder="76" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-xl border border-slate-300 p-3 text-base outline-none focus:border-indigo-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-100" /></label>
      <label class="block"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-700">Formula</span>
        <select id="div" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-xl border border-slate-300 p-3 outline-none focus:border-indigo-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-100">
          <option value="9.5">CBSE (÷ 9.5)</option>
          <option value="10">÷ 10</option>
          <option value="custom">Custom divisor</option>
        </select></label>
      <label id="custom-wrap" class="block sm:max-w-[12rem]" style="display:none"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-700">Custom divisor</span>
        <input id="custom" type="number" step="any" value="9.5" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-xl border border-slate-300 p-3 outline-none focus:border-indigo-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-100" /></label>
    </div>

    <div id="result" class="mt-6 hidden rounded-xl bg-indigo-600 p-5 text-center text-white">
      <div class="text-sm opacity-80">Your CGPA</div>
      <div id="cgpa" class="mt-1 text-3xl font-bold">—</div>
      <div id="formula" class="mt-1 font-mono text-sm opacity-80"></div>
    </div>
    <p id="hint" class="mt-4 text-center text-sm text-slate-400">Enter your percentage to convert it to CGPA.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">How percentage to CGPA conversion works</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Converting percentage to CGPA is the reverse of CGPA to percentage. The formula is <code>CGPA = Percentage ÷ Divisor</code>. Using the standard CBSE divisor of 9.5, a 76% score converts to 76 ÷ 9.5 = 8.0 CGPA. This is the same relationship used by CBSE and many Indian institutions.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
      The divisor represents the average percentage that corresponds to one CGPA point. CBSE determined 9.5 as the divisor by analyzing score distributions — on average, students earned about 9.5% per CGPA point. Different boards may use different divisors, and some use a lookup table rather than a single formula. Our calculator supports the standard CBSE divisor, ×10, and any custom divisor your institution specifies.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Worked examples</h3>
      <div class="mt-2 grid gap-2 text-sm sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">85% ÷ 9.5:</span> <span class="text-slate-600">85 ÷ 9.5 = <strong>8.95 CGPA</strong></span></div>
        <div><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">76% ÷ 9.5:</span> <span class="text-slate-600">76 ÷ 9.5 = <strong>8.00 CGPA</strong></span></div>
        <div><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">90% ÷ 10:</span> <span class="text-slate-600">90 ÷ 10 = <strong>9.00 CGPA</strong></span></div>
        <div><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">62% ÷ custom 9.0:</span> <span class="text-slate-600">62 ÷ 9.0 = <strong>6.89 CGPA</strong></span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <figure class="mt-10">
    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 800 200" width="800" height="200" role="img" aria-labelledby="p2c-title p2c-desc">
      <title id="p2c-title">Percentage to CGPA Conversion Scale</title>
      <desc id="p2c-desc">A dual-scale diagram showing percentage on top mapped to CGPA on bottom using the CBSE divisor of 9.5</desc>
      <rect x="50" y="30" width="700" height="36" rx="6" fill="#ecfdf5" />
      <text x="50" y="54" fill="#059669" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="700">Percentage</text>
      <text x="120" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">0%</text>
      <text x="256" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">19%</text>
      <text x="393" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">38%</text>
      <text x="529" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">57%</text>
      <text x="666" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">76%</text>
      <line x1="50" y1="75" x2="750" y2="75" stroke="#a7f3d0" stroke-width="2" />

      <rect x="50" y="90" width="700" height="36" rx="6" fill="#e0e7ff" />
      <text x="50" y="114" fill="#4338ca" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="700">CGPA</text>
      <text x="120" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">0</text>
      <text x="256" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">2</text>
      <text x="393" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">4</text>
      <text x="529" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">6</text>
      <text x="666" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">8</text>
      <line x1="50" y1="135" x2="750" y2="135" stroke="#c7d2fe" stroke-width="2" />

      <line x1="666" y1="75" x2="666" y2="90" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4" />
      <rect x="610" y="138" width="112" height="28" rx="4" fill="#6366f1" />
      <text x="666" y="157" text-anchor="middle" fill="#fff" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13" font-weight="600">76% = 8.0 CGPA</text>
      <polygon points="666,130 656,138 676,138" fill="#6366f1" />
    </svg>
    <figcaption class="mt-2 text-center text-sm text-slate-500">Percentage is converted to CGPA by dividing by the standard CBSE divisor of 9.5</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Common percentage ranges and their CGPA</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">See how different percentage scores translate into CGPA using the standard CBSE divisor.</p>
    <div class="mt-5 space-y-3">
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">90–100%</span><span class="text-slate-400">9.5–10.5 CGPA — Outstanding</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-emerald-500" style="width:95%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">80–89%</span><span class="text-slate-400">8.4–9.4 CGPA — Excellent</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-indigo-500" style="width:84%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">70–79%</span><span class="text-slate-400">7.4–8.3 CGPA — Good</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-indigo-500" style="width:74%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">60–69%</span><span class="text-slate-400">6.3–7.3 CGPA — Satisfactory</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-amber-500" style="width:63%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">50–59%</span><span class="text-slate-400">5.3–6.2 CGPA — Passing</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-orange-500" style="width:53%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">Below 50%</span><span class="text-slate-400">Below 5.3 CGPA — Needs improvement</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500" style="width:45%"></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
      <span class="text-2xl">🎓</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Students</h3>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Convert your percentage marks to CGPA for university applications, scholarship forms, and situations where CGPA is required instead of a percentage.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
      <span class="text-2xl">📝</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Job Applicants</h3>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Some employers ask for your CGPA rather than a percentage. Convert your marks to match their application format quickly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
      <span class="text-2xl">🏫</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Teachers & Counselors</h3>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Help students understand how their percentage scores translate to CGPA for competitive exams, higher education admissions, and career planning.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
      <span class="text-2xl">🌐</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">International Applicants</h3>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">If you studied under a percentage system and need to submit CGPA for an international application, this calculator gives you a quick reference.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-slate-200">
    <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
      <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-slate-500"><tr><th class="p-3">Percentage</th><th class="p-3">÷ 9.5 (CBSE)</th><th class="p-3">÷ 10</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100 text-slate-700">
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">95%</td><td class="p-3">10.0</td><td class="p-3">9.5</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">85%</td><td class="p-3">8.9</td><td class="p-3">8.5</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">76%</td><td class="p-3">8.0</td><td class="p-3">7.6</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">66%</td><td class="p-3">6.9</td><td class="p-3">6.6</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">57%</td><td class="p-3">6.0</td><td class="p-3">5.7</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">47%</td><td class="p-3">4.9</td><td class="p-3">4.7</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">38%</td><td class="p-3">4.0</td><td class="p-3">3.8</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">How to use the percentage to CGPA calculator</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-center">
        <span class="inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700">1</span>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Enter your percentage</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Type in your percentage score (e.g. 76). The calculator accepts any positive number.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-center">
        <span class="inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700">2</span>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Select a divisor</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Choose CBSE (÷9.5), ÷10, or select "Custom divisor" to enter your institution's specific factor.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-center">
        <span class="inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700">3</span>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Get your CGPA</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Your CGPA is displayed instantly with the calculation shown, making it easy to verify the result.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Tips for accurate conversion</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Verify your institution's divisor</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">The CBSE divisor of 9.5 is the most common, but different boards and universities use different values. Check your academic regulations for the official factor.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Double-check for official use</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">This calculator provides an accurate estimate. For official submissions, confirm the conversion method with your target institution or employer.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Reverse conversion</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Need to convert CGPA back to percentage? Use our <a href="/tools/cgpa-to-percentage" class="font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline">CGPA to Percentage Calculator</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">When to use percentage to CGPA conversion</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Converting percentage to CGPA is most commonly needed by students who studied under a percentage-based grading system and need their scores in CGPA format. This happens frequently during college admissions, scholarship applications, and job applications where institutions outside India or specific universities require CGPA rather than raw percentage marks. For example, a student who scored 76% in their Class XII board exams may need to report an 8.0 CGPA when applying to a university that follows the 10-point scale. Similarly, graduate applicants converting their undergraduate scores often need percentage to CGPA conversion for their statement of purpose and application forms.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
      Another common scenario is during campus placements where companies ask for CGPA instead of percentage. A software engineer applying to a multinational company may see a job requirement stating a minimum 7.5 CGPA, but their degree only reports percentage scores. The calculator handles this conversion instantly, allowing the applicant to verify eligibility before applying. Teachers and academic counselors also use this tool regularly to help students understand how their percentage performance translates to the CGPA scale used by competitive exams and higher education institutions across India and abroad.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Why accurate percentage to CGPA conversion matters</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Accuracy in percentage to CGPA conversion is critical because even a small error can change your eligibility for a university program or job application. Many institutions set strict minimum CGPA thresholds for admission. For example, if a course requires a minimum 6.5 CGPA, and your conversion uses the wrong divisor, you could mistakenly think you are ineligible when you actually qualify, or worse, apply believing you meet the requirement when you do not. The difference between a divisor of 9.5 and 9.0 can change a 62% score from a 6.53 CGPA to a 6.89 CGPA, which may cross an important cutoff.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
      Different examination boards and universities use different conversion factors. CBSE uses 9.5, but the Gujarat Board uses 9.0, and some universities use a table-based system instead of a fixed divisor. Using the wrong standard can produce a CGPA that differs significantly from the official value. This calculator lets you select the exact divisor your institution requires, ensuring your conversion matches the official method. For scholarships and competitive admissions, even a few decimal points can determine whether an application advances or is rejected, making accurate conversion an essential step in the process.
    </p>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    const el = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
    el('div').addEventListener('change', () => {
      el('custom-wrap').style.display = el('div').value === 'custom' ? 'block' : 'none';
      update();
    });
    function update() {
      const pct = parseFloat(el('pct').value);
      const d = el('div').value === 'custom' ? parseFloat(el('custom').value) : parseFloat(el('div').value);
      if (isNaN(pct) || isNaN(d) || d === 0) { el('result').classList.add('hidden'); el('hint').classList.remove('hidden'); return; }
      const cgpa = pct / d;
      el('cgpa').textContent = (Math.round(cgpa * 100) / 100).toString();
      el('formula').textContent = `${pct} ÷ ${d} = ${Math.round(cgpa * 100) / 100}`;
      el('result').classList.remove('hidden'); el('hint').classList.add('hidden');
    }
    ['pct', 'custom'].forEach((id) => el(id).addEventListener('input', update));
  </script>
</ToolLayout>
